<item>
            <title>[LU-14896] &apos;lfs migrate -p &lt;pool&gt; &lt;file&gt;&apos; should migrate file to pool with default layout arg</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14896</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&quot;lfs migrate&quot; with only &quot;--pool/-p&quot; argument does not migrate file to pool. It initiate a migration but with the layout of source file (llapi_layout_get_by_path).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When a pool is full and we want to initiate migrations , the behavior is the opposite than expected:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the migrations create volatiles on the source pool, so the space uses on the full pool increase temporally&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it does not migrate files to the specified pool.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
